The paper proposes a model-based framework for generating stable biped locomotion, which involves planning and control. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of Model Predictive Control (MPC), which is a popular technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of obstacle avoidance, which is a common topic in Computer Vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO and cs.SY, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.CV.
